:"Rolvenden, Kent, England","England":"Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Rolvenden, Kent, England":"Rolvenden, Kent, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"Abt 1360–Abt 1394":"about 1360–about 1394","1360–1394":"1360–1394","1346–1411":"1346–1411","1385–1449":"1385–1449","1331–Male":"1331–Deceased","1338–1365":"1338–1365","1338":"1338","Abt 1394":"about 1394","Abt 1360":"about 1360","1346":"1346","1411":"1411","1388":"1388","1365":"1365","1331":"1331","1385":"1385","1394":"1394","1360":"1360","1449":"1449","Halden Manor, Rolvenden, Kent, England":"Rolvenden, Kent, England","England":"England, United Kingdom","Rolvenden, Kent, England":"Rolvenden, Kent, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Guildford","type":"LAST","meanings":["Gild-ford, from gild, a guild, society, or club where money was paid for support, and ford, a ford, meaning a stock ford"],"variants":[]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When William Guildford was born about 1360, in Rolvenden, Kent, England, United Kingdom, his father, Edward Guildford, was 30 and his mother, Alice Sambourne, was 23. He had at least 1 son with Joan de Haldan. In 1388, at the age of 29, his occupation is listed as high sheriff of kent. He died about 1394, in England, United Kingdom, at the age of 36."},"et":{"Abt 1360–Abt 1394":"umbes 1360–umbes 1394","1360–1394":"1360–1394","1346–1411":"1346–1411","1385–1449":"1385–1449","1331–Male":"1331–Surnud","1338–1365":"1338–1365","1338":"1338","Abt 1394":"umbes 1394","Abt 1360":"umbes 1360","1346":"1346","1411":"1411","1388":"1388","1365":"1365","1331":"1331","1385":"1385","1394":"1394","1360":"1360","1449":"1449","Halden Manor, Rolvenden, Kent, England":"Rolvenden, Kent, England","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Rolvenden, Kent, England":"Rolvenden, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1360–Abt 1394":"noin 1360–noin 1394","1360–1394":"1360–1394","1346–1411":"1346–1411","1385–1449":"1385–1449","1331–Male":"1331–Kuollut","1338–1365":"1338–1365","1338":"1338","Abt 1394":"noin 1394","Abt 1360":"noin 1360","1346":"1346","1411":"1411","1388":"1388","1365":"1365","1331":"1331","1385":"1385","1394":"1394","1360":"1360","1449":"1449","Halden Manor, Rolvenden, Kent, England":"Rolvenden, Kent, England","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Rolvenden, Kent, England":"Rolvenden, Kent, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1360–Abt 1394":"environ 1360–environ 1394","1360–1394":"1360–1394","1346–1411":"1346–1411","1385–1449":"1385–1449","1331–Male":"1331–Décédé","1338–1365":"1338–1365","1338":"1338","Abt 1394":"environ 1394","Abt 1360":"environ 1360","1346":"1346","1411":"1411","1388":"1388","1365":"1365","1331":"1331","1385":"1385","1394":"1394","1360":"1360","1449":"1449","Halden Manor, Rolvenden, Kent, England":"Rolvenden, Kent, Angleterre","England":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Rolvenden, Kent, England":"Rolvenden, Kent, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Lorsque William Guildford est né environ 1360, à Rolvenden, Kent, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, son père, Edward Guildford, avait 30 ans et sa mère, Alice Sambourne, avait 23 ans. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Joan de Haldan. En 1388, à l’âge de 29 ans, sa profession de son indiquée est high sheriff of kent. Il est décédé env